From: Hector Martin <marcan@marcan.st>
Date: Wed, 15 May 2024 18:15:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: hci_bcm4377: Fix msgid release
Git-commit: 897e6120566f1c108b85fefe78d1c1bddfbd5988
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc7
References: git-fixes

We are releasing a single msgid, so the order argument to
bitmap_release_region must be zero.

Fixes: 8a06127602de ("Bluetooth: hci_bcm4377: Add new driver for BCM4377 PCIe boards")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Hector Martin <marcan@marcan.st>
Reviewed-by: Sven Peter <sven@svenpeter.dev>
Reviewed-by: Neal Gompa <neal@gompa.dev>
Signed-off-by: Sven Peter <sven@svenpeter.dev>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/bluetooth/hci_bcm4377.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/hci_bcm4377.c b/drivers/bluetooth/hci_bcm4377.c
index 94e736595443..d90858ea2fe5 100644
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/hci_bcm4377.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/hci_bcm4377.c
@@ -721,7 +721,7 @@ static void bcm4377_handle_ack(struct bcm4377_data *bcm4377,
 		ring->events[msgid] = NULL;
 	}
 
-	bitmap_release_region(ring->msgids, msgid, ring->n_entries);
+	bitmap_release_region(ring->msgids, msgid, 0);
 
 unlock:
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ring->lock, flags);
